    "abstract": "<jats:p> We provide a result on prospect theory decision makers who are na\u00efve about the time inconsistency induced by probability weighting. If a market offers a sufficiently rich set of investment strategies, investors postpone their trading decisions indefinitely due to a strong preference for skewness. We conclude that probability weighting in combination with na\u00efvet\u00e9 leads to unrealistic predictions for a wide range of dynamic setups. (JEL D81, G02, G11) </jats:p>",
